Say "yo" to baby_yoda, the newest Citizen of the Week. <br><br>Sometimes known as <b>Yoda Jr</b>., there is nothing junior about his presence or his home! We soon realized that his bright clothing perfectly matched his bright personality. Wearing a golden crown and yellow cape, he was impossible to miss, and impossible not to crown Citizen of the Week.<br><br>He lives at <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=baby_yoda"><a href='/home/?user=baby_yoda'>42020-D Main Street</a>, Metro Park</a> and has been a citizen since April 20, 2008. We urge you take a peak at his three-floored home with five gardens. This is where he keeps his 65 trophies! Yes, we said 65! It's no surprise that he's very athletic and sporty. What makes baby_yoda even more appealing is that he's easy going. His interests include drawing, and soccer. But he will only draw with gold and blue crayons. In his spare time, he likes to hang out at the Amusement Park&mdash;which he uses as inspiration as he adds onto his majestic home.  If you want an invite to his annual New Year's Eve party, buy him some New Wave, Pop, or Reggae CDs!  <br></div>
